HHexen ChangeLog

v1.4.1
 - Added support for the Mac version of the
   demo hexen.wad file.
 - The demo wad files support doesn't need a
   special configuration anymore.
 - Various hacks and/or fixes for the proper
   handling of different 1.0 and 1.1, demo or
   retail wad files (see the WADFILES document
   for technical details.)
 - Many other bugfixes

v1.4
 - Configs and savegames stored in ~/.hhexen/
 - SDL and SDL/GL support
 - X11 and SVGALib targets are removed
 - OpenGL screenshots (now bound to F12)
 - Screenshots are now saved to ~/.hhexen/
 - Transparent map feature (TAB key)
 - Fixed broken keybinding in the menu
 - More complete support for punctuation keys
   in the control-setup menu.
 - The config files from the previous hhexen
   versions are now invalid: delete your configs
   and bind your keys again from the menu system.
 - Many GCC/C/portability bugfixes

v1.3
 - OpenGL support
 - Key configuration menu
 - Mouselook and inverse mouselook
 - Autorun

v1.2
 - Sprites load from assassin.wad file
 - Works with Linux Hexen 0.5.0 code

v1.0
 - Initial release
